node.text:
As we continue the celebration of the 20th anniversary of Hybrid Theory, we also wanted to celebrate the beginning of our fan club: Linkin Park Underground.
 
We released the very first Linkin Park Underground bundle to the LPU community on November 19, 2001. Fast forward to the present day, we are releasing LPU 20 which is heavily inspired by the design of archived items from LPU1.
 
Members with an LPU Full Access account can now shop the exclusive LPU 20 bundle + merchandise.

LPU Community Members and non-members can sign up at LPUnderground.com.

node.text:
Happy 9th Anniversary to A Thousand Suns. Check out our very first live performance of "The Catalyst" from the 2010 VMAs at the iconic Griffith Observatory in Los Angeles.

Stream / Download 'A Thousand Suns' --> link in bio

node.title: The Catalyst (Live at the 2010 MTV VMAs) - Linkin Park

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by LINKIN PARK on September 14, 2021 tagging @gregwatermann. May be an image of 1 person, camera and text.

node.text:
A Thousand Suns turns 11 today 🎉  Here are some bts photos from The Catalyst music video directed by @mrjoehahn 

“The Catalyst video was an illustration of dark frustration with dramatic release of tension. As seen with Chester practically drowning while singing or Mike guised as this mysterious figure who boldly speaks while in hiding in a dystopian setting. For myself, this song represented a lot of what I felt A Thousand Suns was about. The album is a journey dealing with the mistakes of our past and currently digging through the mess of what we created as a society. There is a light at the end of that tunnel of despair. This is illustrated by the throwing of colored dust. It has a riotous angry mosh pit vibe while simultaneously celebratory. Basically, a beautiful mess and one of my favorite music videos.” - @mrjoehahn 

📸: @gregwatermann
